					span.r-card__header A difficult adjustment to holidaying in Dubai
					.r-card__text
						p  The social environment seems unfriendly and overloaded with irrelevant offers. Instead of experiencing positive emotions, a person gets stuck in problems of search, socialization and everyday life, instead of resting or pursuing their goals.
				.item.r-card.r-card_ext
					span.r-card__header Stagnation of the entertainment market
					.r-card__text
						p  Small companies, being overshadowed by big brands, go unnoticed by their customers. Similarly, consumers with modest income levels do not find suitable offers. The quality of the market suffers from significant competitive inequality and lack of choices in the information field.
				.item.r-card.r-card_ext
					span.r-card__header Hidden threat to society
					.r-card__text
						p  WHO experts predict that depression will become a key cause of disability, ranking second after cardiovascular pathology. The problem of loneliness is relevant worldwide, for example, according to the ONS, 29% of Britons spend their leisure time alone.
				.item.r-card.r-card_ext
					span.r-card__header Large quantity does not mean quality
					.r-card__text
						p  A large number of places and events does not mean the quality of each of them. 
							br
							| According to DET, only 3 % of restaurants meet high quality standards. The same can be assumed for other types of places or leisure activities. There may be enough human traffic for everyone, but it does not mean that people will be satisfied.

		section.inf-list 
